===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `cowpoke` command is used to send messages to other users on the network.  You can direct a message to a specific user or broadcast it to all active users. This command is mostly used in terminal environments.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `cowpoke <username> <message>` --> 🗣️ Send a message to a specific user.  You must enter the username and the text of the message.
    🔹 `cowpoke -a <message>`      --> 📢 Send a message to all active users on the system.
    🔹 `cowpoke -n <username>`  --> 👤 Announce login to user named <username>.
    🔹 `cowpoke -q <username>`  --> 👋🏻 Announce logout to user named <username>.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ cowpoke ali hello ali! how are you?

    🔹 Sends the message "hello ali! how are you?" to the user "ali".

    $ cowpoke -a hello everyone! good morning!

    🔹 Sends the message "hello everyone! good morning!" to all active users.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ cowpoke -n nima

    🔹 Announce login to user with username "nima", this user will know that you have logged in.

